# Planning

Specs, ADRs, and design discussion for {{PROJECT_NAME}}. Thinking room - no code lives here.

## Templates
Copy from `templates/`, rename, and fill in. Don't edit the templates themselves.
- `templates/spec-template.md` - feature/component specs
- `templates/adr-template.md` - architecture decisions

## File types
- `*-spec_draft.md` / `*-spec_final.md` - design specs
- `adr-NNN-<topic>_<status>.md` - architecture decision records (numbered, dated, context > decision > consequences)
- `*.mmd` or fenced ` ```mermaid ` blocks - diagrams

## Rules
- Specs name the problem, the chosen approach, and what was rejected and why.
- ADRs are dated and numbered sequentially.
- No implementation code in specs - that belongs in a build room.
- Anything > ~50 lines of code needs a spec or ADR here first.
- Promotion trigger: when an item appears in two `Promotion candidates` tables across rooms, formalize it as a skill, agent, or shared module.

